{"id":"rr-002","title":"Domain and storage","description":"Define the durable Roger data model for sessions, runs, findings, artifacts, approval-safe outbound communication, scope/memory overlays, and rebuildable search sidecars before UI work spreads. This epic must lock the canonical local-first store shape, write-ownership rules, and migration boundaries so later CLI, TUI, and extension work do not invent conflicting state models or daemon-like coordination assumptions.","acceptance_criteria":"Core entities, invariants, and aggregate boundaries are explicit for sessions, findings, evidence, drafts, approvals, posted actions, scope, and index state\nWrite-ownership, row-version or conflict rules, and append-only event-history expectations are defined before concurrent surfaces are implemented\nStorage, migration, artifact, and rebuildable search-sidecar boundaries are explicit enough that later work cannot smuggle mutable review state into derived indices or extension-local caches","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:42.214322Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["epic","planning","storage"]}
{"id":"rr-003","title":"Harness session orchestration","description":"Define and implement Roger's supported-harness linkage so Roger can add structure without breaking plain OpenCode fallback, while keeping Gemini support bounded and truthful. This epic must make the provider boundary operational rather than aspirational: Roger should reference underlying provider sessions explicitly, preserve a real bare-harness return path, and avoid turning provider adapters into the hidden architecture center.","acceptance_criteria":"Harness linkage boundary, capability tiers, and continuity-quality rules are explicit for OpenCode primary and Gemini bounded support\nOpenCode fallback, dropout, and return behavior are implemented and testable before downstream surfaces claim resume support\nRoger metadata references underlying provider sessions and ResumeBundle state directly rather than hiding them behind fake parity or daemon-only assumptions","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:50.728535Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["epic","harness","planning","sessions"]}
{"id":"rr-003.1","title":"Implement OpenCode primary adapter, bare-harness dropout, and rr return","description":"Implement the real OpenCode path Roger is planning around: provider session start/reopen, ResumeBundle reseed fallback, intentional dropout to plain OpenCode, and explicit return back into Roger. This bead exists because defining the contract alone is not enough; CLI, TUI, and browser-launch claims are not truthful until the primary adapter and fallback loop are operational.","acceptance_criteria":"OpenCode-backed reviews can start or reopen through a SessionLocator when available and fall back to ResumeBundle reseed when direct reopen is unavailable\nIntentional dropout preserves the Roger control bundle needed to continue safely in plain OpenCode without losing review target or safety posture\nrr return or equivalent helper rebinds the bare harness session to the correct Roger session, with auto-return on harness exit treated only as a convenience path\nSmoke coverage proves plain OpenCode fallback and resume behavior are operational rather than marketing language","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:06.983340Z","created_by":"cdilga","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:11.233988Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["harness","opencode","resume","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-003.1","depends_on_id":"rr-003","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:06.983340Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-003.1","depends_on_id":"rr-014","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:06.983340Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-003.1","depends_on_id":"rr-015","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:06.983340Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-003.2","title":"Implement Gemini bounded adapter and truthful reseed path","description":"Implement the bounded Gemini path Roger claims for 0.1.0 without implying OpenCode-level continuity. This bead exists to make Tier A support concrete: Roger owns the continuity ledger, captures raw and structured output, and tells the truth when deeper reopen or in-harness affordances do not exist.","acceptance_criteria":"Gemini-backed reviews can start through Roger and persist both raw output artifacts and structured normalization inputs\nCapability reporting stays bounded to the Tier A contract and rejects direct-resume, dropout, or harness-native command claims when unsupported\nResumeBundle reseed works truthfully when native reopen semantics are unavailable or weaker than OpenCode\nAcceptance coverage proves the bounded Gemini path is useful without parity theater","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:15.704271Z","created_by":"cdilga","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:19.448110Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["gemini","harness","resume","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-003.2","depends_on_id":"rr-003","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:15.704271Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-003.2","depends_on_id":"rr-014","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:15.704271Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-003.2","depends_on_id":"rr-015","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:15.704271Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-004","title":"Prompt pipeline and review engine","description":"Build the staged review workflow that explores first, goes deep second, and persists validated structured findings rather than terminal-only output. This epic must encode prompt invocation snapshots, findings-pack validation, repair boundaries, and refresh-safe lineage so downstream TUI and approval flows never act on ad hoc parser output or mutation-capable shortcuts.","acceptance_criteria":"Prompt stages, invocation snapshots, and structured findings boundaries are explicit and durable\nFindings normalization and repair behavior are validated so malformed provider output degrades honestly instead of fabricating state\nRefresh flows can carry forward, repair, or retire findings coherently without bypassing validation or mutating outbound state implicitly","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:55.402011Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["epic","planning","review-engine"]}
{"id":"rr-004.1","title":"Implement structured findings pack validator and repair boundary","description":"Define and implement the StructuredFindingsPack v1 boundary Roger relies on for durable findings, refresh identity, and safe outbound drafting. This bead exists because prompt stages are not enough; Roger needs a validator, salvage rules, and bounded repair behavior so malformed provider output cannot silently manufacture findings or drafts.","acceptance_criteria":"A stable StructuredFindingsPack v1 schema, validator, and normalization boundary into Roger-owned finding rows are explicit\nMalformed or partial findings packs follow a bounded repair taxonomy with salvage rules and retry budget rather than ad hoc parser recovery\nRaw-only degraded results are preserved and surfaced locally without synthesizing fake findings, fake evidence, or outbound drafts\nIntegration coverage proves refresh and draft-generation paths consume only validated findings state","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:23.413695Z","created_by":"cdilga","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:31.613485Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["findings","normalization","repair","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-004.1","depends_on_id":"rr-004","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:23.413695Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-004.1","depends_on_id":"rr-013","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:23.413695Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-004.1","depends_on_id":"rr-014","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:36:23.413695Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-005","title":"Session-aware CLI","description":"Provide the shell entrypoint for starting, resuming, returning to, inspecting, and refreshing Roger review sessions using repo context where possible. This epic must keep the extension-free path first-class and must expose the durable control surface Roger relies on for OpenCode fallback, approval-safe review work, and future bounded robot-facing output.","acceptance_criteria":"Review, resume, return, findings, and status flows work from the shell without the browser extension installed\nRepo-context inference resolves a target only when it can do so safely and never silently retargets drafts or approvals\nCLI remains Roger-owned and approval-safe: mutation-capable posting stays visibly elevated and cannot bypass the local draft model","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:37:00.256647Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cli","epic","planning"]}
{"id":"rr-006","title":"TUI workflow","description":"Implement the main Roger TUI for session navigation, findings triage, refresh-aware evidence inspection, and local-only approval of outbound GitHub drafts. This epic must keep approval and posting visibly elevated, preserve daemonless local-first behavior, and avoid turning the extension into the real workflow while the TUI stays half-formed.","acceptance_criteria":"Active review sessions, findings, evidence links, and refresh lineage are navigable in the TUI without needing the browser extension\nOutbound drafts are reviewed, edited, approved, rejected, or invalidated locally, with no hidden GitHub write path from ordinary finding views\nTUI refresh behavior relies on Roger-owned store or event state rather than a resident broker or extension-owned cache","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:37:08.872742Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["epic","planning","tui"]}
{"id":"rr-007","title":"GitHub integration and extension","description":"Add GitHub-targeted adapters and the browser entry surface without letting the extension become the system control plane, state owner, or an approval bypass. This epic must keep Native Messaging as the serious on-demand bridge, custom URL as convenience only, and all GitHub mutation flowing through Roger-owned draft and approval contracts.","acceptance_criteria":"GitHub adapter behavior is explicit and consumes Roger-owned draft objects rather than ambient current-PR state or raw gh comment commands\nBrowser launch or resume is validated through a daemonless bridge with Native Messaging primary and custom URL limited to thin launch or recovery behavior\nExtension UI remains a thin surface over Roger core with bounded status reads and no posting or approval authority of its own","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:37:13.532444Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["epic","extension","github","planning"]}
{"id":"rr-008","title":"Approval and posting flow","description":"Model and implement the local draft and approval path for comments, questions, and suggestions before any GitHub mutation occurs. This epic is the hard safety boundary for Roger: no raw review communication via gh, no ambient current-PR posting, and no reuse of stale approval after payload, target, refresh, or instance changes.","acceptance_criteria":"Outbound drafts and batches are explicit local objects tied to one review target and one Roger session\nApproval is required before posting and binds to exact payload and target identity rather than a generic ready-to-post flag\nRefresh, rebase, retarget, or worktree or instance changes invalidate affected approvals automatically before the posting path is available again","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:37:18.621186Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["approval","epic","planning"]}
{"id":"rr-009","title":"Worktrees and named instances","description":"Support isolated review work via worktrees and conservative named-instance sharing without overengineering the first version.","acceptance_criteria":"- Review environments can be isolated safely\\n- Multiple named instances can coexist\\n- State-sharing strategy is conservative and explicit","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["epic","planning","worktrees"]}
{"id":"rr-010","title":"Hybrid search, memory, and skills","description":"Add the repo-first retrieval layer for prior findings, searchable artifacts, and semantic review memory using hybrid lexical plus semantic search from day one, while keeping scope and promotion rules explicit.","acceptance_criteria":"Hybrid lexical plus semantic retrieval exists for 0.1.0 with truthful lexical-only degraded mode; Prior review lookup helps refresh flows and memory stays scope-safe; Later memory and promotion workflows remain isolated behind stable interfaces","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T07:32:09.268387Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["epic","hybrid-search","memory","planning","search"]}
{"id":"rr-011","title":"Safety and validation","description":"Prove the product stays review-safe, approval-gated, scope-safe, daemonless in steady state, and resumable through explicit validation rather than assumptions. This epic should encode the small but real automated and manual matrix Roger needs before implementation can claim OpenCode fallback, bounded Gemini support, Edge bridge support, or approval-safe posting.","acceptance_criteria":"Review-safe defaults, approval invalidation, and cross-review posting protection are exercised explicitly rather than inferred from design docs\nOpenCode dropout and return, bounded Gemini acceptance, refresh identity, and daemonless bridge behavior all have repeatable smoke or acceptance coverage\nThe support matrix distinguishes blessed paths from weaker degraded paths so Roger does not make fake parity claims across providers, browsers, or platforms","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:37:26.930554Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["epic","planning","safety","validation"]}
{"id":"rr-012","title":"Run architecture risk spikes and capture ADRs","description":"Reduce the highest-risk unknowns before implementation spreads: the supported-harness contract, browser bridge, local runtime/process boundary, and artifact/storage split. Record any package-shaping outcomes in ADRs.","acceptance_criteria":"Spike outcomes are documented; Any package-shaping decisions are captured in ADRs; The harness capability tiers, browser bridge, and artifact/storage assumptions are no longer implicit","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T10:16:45.389996Z","closed_at":"2026-03-29T10:16:45.389607Z","close_reason":"Closed by Round 04 reconciliation outcome: architecture spikes were run, accepted ADRs exist, and the formerly implicit assumptions are now explicit in canonical docs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"pinned":true,"labels":["adr","planning","spike"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-012","depends_on_id":"rr-001","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-013","title":"Define core domain schema and finding fingerprint model","description":"Specify the first-class entities for sessions, runs, findings, finding fingerprints, SessionLocator and ResumeBundle state, artifacts, outbound drafts and batches, prompt invocations, posted actions, scope and memory records, and config layers. Include refresh identity, write-ownership, event-history, approval-binding, and scope-boundary rules needed to avoid duplicate explosions, silent bleed, or mutation-capable state that bypasses Roger control.","acceptance_criteria":"Core entities and invariants are defined, including prompt invocations, draft batches, approval tokens, attention state, and the SessionLocator versus ResumeBundle split.\nTriage state, outbound state, append-only event history, and session-level write ownership are explicit, including same-session conflict handling and background-index ownership.\nFinding fingerprint, refresh classification, scope-boundary rules, and repo or project or org overlay policy are explicit, and no mutation-capable state bypasses Roger-owned approval records.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:54.230688Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"pinned":true,"labels":["domain","findings","planning"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-013","depends_on_id":"rr-002","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-014","title":"Implement local storage, migrations, and artifact budget classes","description":"Create the canonical SQLite-family persistence layer, migration flow, row-version or conflict scheme, and artifact split Roger needs for local-first review state. This task must preserve hot-path responsiveness for CLI, TUI, and bridge flows while keeping large artifacts and rebuildable search assets out of mutable core review tables.","acceptance_criteria":"Migration flow exists for the canonical Roger aggregates and includes explicit row-version or conflict behavior for same-session writes\nStorage schema supports sessions, runs, findings, drafts, approvals, posted actions, launch profiles, and index bookkeeping without hiding mutable state in sidecars\nArtifact budget classes and cold-storage rules prevent large payloads from bloating primary tables while preserving provenance and rebuild semantics for search sidecars","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:37:32.633030Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["artifacts","fts","storage"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-014","depends_on_id":"rr-002","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-014","depends_on_id":"rr-013","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-015","title":"Define the Roger-to-harness session linkage","description":"Define the exact Roger session contract for supported harnesses, with OpenCode primary and Gemini bounded: capability tiers, continuity-quality rules, resume and reseed behavior, dropout semantics, and safe optional harness-native commands. This task fixes the contract that downstream adapters and UI surfaces must implement, so Roger can preserve real fallback and truthful provider claims without depending on fragile provider internals.","acceptance_criteria":"Session linkage, capability tiers, continuity-quality reporting, and ResumeBundle rules are documented and stable enough for adapter implementation\nOpenCode Tier B and Gemini Tier A expectations are explicit, including what Roger may not claim for each provider\nDropout, return, and safe harness-native command rules are fixed without allowing approval or GitHub-posting behavior to hide inside in-harness commands","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:37:37.669783Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"pinned":true,"labels":["harness","opencode","sessions","spike"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-015","depends_on_id":"rr-003","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-015","depends_on_id":"rr-012","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-015","depends_on_id":"rr-013","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-016","title":"Encode staged review prompts and structured findings","description":"Implement the staged review engine around validated prompt invocations and findings-pack normalization, not around raw terminal transcripts alone. This task should orchestrate exploration and deep-review passes, preserve invocation snapshots and evidence lineage, and feed only validated findings state into later refresh, TUI, and approval flows.","acceptance_criteria":"Prompt stages are executable independently and each invocation preserves the resolved prompt snapshot, stage metadata, and raw artifact linkage\nStructured outputs are normalized only through the validated findings-pack boundary, with degraded raw-only outcomes surfaced honestly when validation cannot recover\nEvidence links, stage provenance, and non-mutating review posture are retained so later outbound drafting cannot happen from unvalidated or mutation-biased output","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:38:59.563600Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["findings","prompts","review-engine"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-016","depends_on_id":"rr-004","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-016","depends_on_id":"rr-004.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:38:59.563108Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-016","depends_on_id":"rr-014","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-016","depends_on_id":"rr-015","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-017","title":"Implement refresh behavior and finding lifecycle transitions","description":"Support reruns after new commits by classifying findings as carried forward, superseded, resolved, stale, or revalidated instead of duplicating them blindly. This task must preserve outbound and approval lineage honestly: refresh should never silently retarget an approved draft or make a stale finding look newly discovered.","acceptance_criteria":"Refresh maps new findings to prior findings through explicit fingerprint and evidence rules rather than fuzzy ad hoc matching\nLifecycle transitions cover carried-forward, superseded, resolved, stale, and approval-invalidating changes with deterministic state rules\nRefresh output preserves lineage needed for TUI history and blocks stale approval or posting when the underlying target, payload, or evidence meaning has changed","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:01.854471Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["findings","identity","refresh"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-017","depends_on_id":"rr-004","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-017","depends_on_id":"rr-004.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:01.853946Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-017","depends_on_id":"rr-013","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-017","depends_on_id":"rr-016","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-018","title":"Implement session-aware CLI review, resume, findings, status, and refresh","description":"Create the CLI layer that can infer repo context where possible and drive the usable Roger review loop without relying on the extension. This task must make the shell path real for the primary OpenCode workflow, including review, resume, return, findings, status, and refresh, while staying honest about provider support and never bypassing the approval model.","acceptance_criteria":"Review, resume, return, findings, status, and refresh commands work from the shell on the blessed OpenCode path without the extension installed\nRepo-context inference resolves PR targets only when safe and never silently reuses or retargets stale drafts, approvals, or sessions\nCLI output surfaces degraded or unsupported provider capabilities truthfully and keeps posting or other mutation-capable actions behind Roger's explicit draft and approval flow","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:08.786715Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["cli","session-aware"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-018","depends_on_id":"rr-003.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:08.786158Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-018","depends_on_id":"rr-005","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-018","depends_on_id":"rr-015","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-018","depends_on_id":"rr-016","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-018","depends_on_id":"rr-017","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-019","title":"Build the TUI findings workflow and local approval surfaces","description":"Implement the main Roger TUI shell, findings list and detail flow, evidence navigation, history or refresh context, and local approval surface for outbound GitHub drafts. This task must reinforce the product's local-first safety posture: users triage and approve locally, while GitHub posting remains a visibly elevated next step rather than an inline shortcut.","acceptance_criteria":"Users can enter an active review session, inspect findings and evidence, and understand refresh lineage or degraded state directly in the TUI\nFindings can be triaged quickly without triggering GitHub mutation or collapsing approval into ordinary navigation gestures\nOutbound drafts can be reviewed, edited, approved, rejected, or invalidated locally before any posting path is exposed","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:38:05.301809Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["approval","findings","tui"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-019","depends_on_id":"rr-006","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-019","depends_on_id":"rr-018","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-019","depends_on_id":"rr-020","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-020","title":"Model outbound drafts and posted-action audit trail","description":"Define the local representation for review comments, questions, and suggestions awaiting approval, including grouped draft batches, approval tokens, invalidation rules, and preservation of the exact payload that was eventually posted. This task is the contract that prevents premature or mis-targeted GitHub mutation across refreshes, rebases, or worktree or instance changes.","acceptance_criteria":"Outbound drafts and draft batches are linked to findings, one Roger session, and one immutable review target tuple\nApproval binds to exact payload hash and target identity, and affected approvals are invalidated on refresh, rebase, retarget, or worktree or instance changes\nPosted payload, posting outcome, and remote identifiers are snapshotted locally so Roger can audit exactly what was approved and what was sent","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:05.901588Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["approval","audit","github"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-020","depends_on_id":"rr-004.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:05.901088Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-020","depends_on_id":"rr-008","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-020","depends_on_id":"rr-013","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-020","depends_on_id":"rr-016","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-021","title":"Implement GitHub adapter and validate the browser launch bridge","description":"Resolve PR metadata locally, prepare outbound actions through a Roger-owned adapter boundary, and validate a daemonless browser-to-local launch or resume flow with Native Messaging primary and custom URL convenience only. This task must not smuggle in direct gh review writes, hidden background services, or extension-owned state that bypasses Roger's local approval model.","acceptance_criteria":"PR targets can be resolved and adapted locally through a Roger-owned adapter that consumes approved draft objects rather than ambient current-PR state or raw gh review-comment commands\nNative Messaging primary bridge works on supported browsers including Edge without a persistent daemon, and custom URL remains a thin convenience or recovery path only\nBridge and adapter degradation paths are truthful, preserve approval safety, and fail closed when approval, target identity, or local Roger availability is missing","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:11.785339Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["bridge","extension","github"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-021","depends_on_id":"rr-003.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:11.784779Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-021","depends_on_id":"rr-007","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-021","depends_on_id":"rr-012","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-021","depends_on_id":"rr-018","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-021","depends_on_id":"rr-020","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-022","title":"Implement extension UI with bounded v1 status behavior","description":"Inject Roger actions into GitHub PR pages, but keep the 0.1.0 extension honest: launch and resume matter most, bounded status is optional, and the extension is never the source of truth for review state or approval. This task should stay intentionally thin so Roger does not drift into a browser-first or hidden-daemon architecture.","acceptance_criteria":"Launch and resume actions are available from GitHub PR pages and route into Roger's approved bridge contracts rather than inventing a second workflow\nStatus or no-status behavior is explicit and bounded for 0.1.0, with no hidden polling daemon or fake parity claims when local Roger state is unavailable\nThe extension cannot approve, post, or mutate review state beyond thin launch and bounded status intents","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:14.813983Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["extension","github","v1-scope"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-022","depends_on_id":"rr-007","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-022","depends_on_id":"rr-019","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:14.813404Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-022","depends_on_id":"rr-021","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-023","title":"Implement worktree preparation and conservative named-instance sharing","description":"Support isolated review environments and multiple named Roger instances, starting with conservative snapshot or copy semantics rather than ambitious fine-grained sync. This task must keep one canonical store per profile as the default, make env-copy and resource-allocation rules explicit, and ensure retargeting or instance moves cannot preserve stale approval state by accident.","acceptance_criteria":"Review worktrees can be prepared, tracked, and torn down with explicit env-copy and mutable-resource rules\nMultiple named instances can coexist safely with conservative sharing semantics for DB, ports, and container or service naming\nInstance or worktree retargeting behavior is explicit and invalidates affected approvals or review bindings when target identity changes","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:23.222633Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["instances","worktrees"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-023","depends_on_id":"rr-009","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-023","depends_on_id":"rr-014","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-023","depends_on_id":"rr-018","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-023","depends_on_id":"rr-020","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:23.222079Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-024","title":"Add hybrid prior-review lookup and memory hooks","description":"Provide fast repo-first retrieval of prior findings and review artifacts using lexical plus semantic search, with truthful lexical-only degraded mode and scope-safe memory hooks for refresh and triage. This task must keep search derived and rebuildable, keep promotion policy separate from retrieval, and avoid scope bleed or approval-sensitive hidden state.","acceptance_criteria":"Prior review lookup is fast, locally queryable, and bounded by explicit repo or project or org scope rules rather than opportunistic fallback\nHybrid retrieval supports refresh and triage with lexical-only degraded mode, rebuild semantics, and no mutation of core review aggregates from index workers\nMemory and promotion hooks remain isolated behind stable interfaces so retrieval can help triage without silently changing approval, finding, or posting state","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:38:41.026898Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["hybrid-search","memory","search"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-024","depends_on_id":"rr-010","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-024","depends_on_id":"rr-014","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-024","depends_on_id":"rr-017","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
{"id":"rr-025","title":"Validate end-to-end review safety, fallback, and refresh identity","description":"Run the validation matrix across CLI launch, TUI triage, GitHub launch, approval-gated posting, supported-harness fallback, refresh identity, and provider acceptance so the planning stage exits with proof rather than optimism. This task should be the place where Roger demonstrates that local-first, daemonless, approval-safe behavior actually survives the real seams between storage, session orchestration, TUI, and extension work.","acceptance_criteria":"CLI, TUI, and GitHub launch paths have repeatable validation steps covering the blessed OpenCode path, bounded Gemini path, and browser bridge truthfulness\nNothing posts without explicit approval: cross-review target mismatch, stale approval after refresh, and missing-local-state cases all fail closed\nOpenCode dropout and rr return, refresh identity carry-forward, and daemonless bridge behavior are exercised explicitly through smoke or acceptance coverage rather than inferred from unit tests alone","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:29.923072Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"pinned":true,"labels":["e2e","safety","support-matrix","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"rr-025","depends_on_id":"rr-003.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:25.324156Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-025","depends_on_id":"rr-003.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:27.792323Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-025","depends_on_id":"rr-004.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-29T11:39:29.922548Z","created_by":"cdilga","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"rr-025","depends_on_id":"rr-011","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-19T22:45:00Z","created_by":"codex","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}